2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
¾ cup Basmati Rice
56 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Tomato
28 g Croutons
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Caesar Dressing
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
5 g Italian Herb Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Lemon
1 tbsp Butter*
1 tsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting wash and dry all produce.
Lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium (approx. 400°F).
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, stir in rice and half the Italian Herb Spice Blend. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, zest, then juice lemon.
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.
Snip one corner of crouton packet. Using a pot or rolling pin, crush croutons into pea-sized crumbs.
To a medium bowl, add mayo, Caesar dressing, Parmesan and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, stir to combine.
To a large bowl, add 2 tbsp (1/4 cup) dressing mixture, tomatoes and spring mix. (NOTE: The salad will be tossed in step 5.)

Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and remaining Italian Herb Spice Blend. Drizzle with 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil. Flip to coat.
Add chicken to the grill. Reduce heat to medium, close lid and grill for 6-8 min per side, until chicken is cooked through.**

When the chicken is done, spread remaining dressing mixture over top, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Close lid and grill for 1-3 min, until cheese melts.
Lightly press crouton topping on the tops of chicken, then set aside for 2 min to rest.

Fluff rice with fork, stir in lemon zest.
Toss salad.
Divide rice, salad and chicken between plates.